ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. Cut back on social activities and entertainment expenses
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened

ElementDescription: 2. Postpone a major household purchase
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened

ElementDescription: 3. Postpone a necessary clothing purchase
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened

ElementDescription: 4. Change transportation patterns to save money
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened

ElementDescription: 5. Change food shopping or eating habits to save money
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened

ElementDescription: 6. Cut back on charitable contributions (e.g. church)
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened

ElementDescription: 7. Reduce household utility use
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened

ElementDescription: 8. Sell some possessions
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened

ElementDescription: 9. I couldn't buy something important because we didn't have enough money
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened; RESPONSES TO STRESS - [FP] (SR-P)

ElementDescription: 10. Things in our home did not work the way they should (no electricity, no water)
Notes: 1=Never Happened, 2=Sometimes Happened, 3=Often Happened, 4=Very Often Happened; RESPONSES TO STRESS - [FP] (SR-P)
